title: 2014 - The Year In Christian Music (Bundle 27)
description:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
2014 - THE YEAR IN CHRISTIAN MUSIC
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Not that I'm losing any sleep over this, but I've always been a little curious about anyone who downloads these bundles for the purpose of keeping the music.  Does it remain in this bundle format on your hard drives?  Are you archiving it into genre groupings?  Or are you creating directories for each of the individual bands, and saving it that way?

ROCK: Amick Cutler, John Riley, Six Days Til Sunday, Voyager.  ALTERNATIVE: Andrew McSunny, Captain Thornton, Jamie N Commons.  FOLK: Bap Kennedy.  PRAISE & WORSHIP: Blessed Music, Ebcworship, Wheaton Class Of 2015 Worship Band.  CONTEMPORARY: Deborah Stanley, Matt Wertz, Paul Fuellbrandt, Provident Music Group.  HIP-HOP/RAP: Dream Junkies, Lil Raskull, MaRLo, Only Human, Thomas T-Dogg Livecchi.  GOSPEL: Gaither Vocal Band, Jovonta Patton, Legacy Five, The Perrys.  SINGER-SONGWRITER: Ian Peacock, Second Hand City.  JAZZ: Lanre Ibk Olowo, Sam Powell.  COUNTRY: Patricia Charlton.  POP: Sam Hart, Waken.  R&B: Victor Chambers.

Our count on the year is now up to 973.
